Plan the Dataflow

Before creating a dataflow, think about its design. Consider what data to make available for queries, where to extract the data from, and whether to transform the extracted data.

To illustrate key design decisions, consider an example: creating a dataset called "Won Opportunities" that contains opportunity details, including account name for each opportunity.

Design this dataflow:

* Extract opportunity data from Opportunity object
* Extract account name from Account object
* Join opportunity and account data into a new dataset
* Filter records based on opportunity stage to include only won opportunities
* Register the final dataset

If you want to flatten your hierarchy, do so before joining datasets.
title: Designing Dataflows in Salesforce Analytics
